# AI Git Commit Policy (Temporary) [CRITICAL]

## Overview
This rule defines the temporary Git commit policy for the AI development team. This policy is in effect until User Story `US-TD-008-ai-git-workflow-and-staging-enhancement.md` is fully implemented.

## Current Policy: Commit to Main Branch [TEMPORARY]

1.  **Default Branch**: All code changes made by the AI development team (all roles) MUST be committed directly to the `main` Git branch.
2.  **No Feature Branches (AI-Led)**: For AI-driven development, separate feature branches are not to be used by default *by the AI itself* at this time. Manual feature branching by the user remains an option.
3.  **Continuous Integration**: Changes committed to `main` should trigger any existing CI/CD processes configured for the `main` branch.

## Future Policy (Reference US-TD-008)
This temporary policy will be replaced by a more robust workflow involving a dedicated AI development branch (e.g., `ai-dev`) and a staging environment, as detailed in `docs/user-stories/backlog/US-TD-008-ai-git-workflow-and-staging-enhancement.md`.

## Enforcement
- All roles, especially the Software Engineering Team (SET) and the Executive Secretary (ES) coordinating commits, MUST adhere to this temporary policy.
- This rule will be updated or superseded upon the completion and implementation of US-TD-008.
